concept.title: RECTANG Command
concept.shortdesc: Creates a polyline in the shape of a rectangle.

conbody.p: Create a closed, four-sided rectangular polyline Insert link to Polyline Entities article in the shape of a rectangle, square, and variants with chamfers or fillets.

section.title: Methods to create a rectangle
section.p: There are five methods to begin creating a rectangle:

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a rectangle by specifying a corner of a rectangle then:
Specify the opposite corner of the rectangle. The rectangle is drawn parallel to the x and y axes.
Begin creating a rectangle by specifying a corner of a rectangle then:
Additional options: [Chamfer/Fillet/Rotated/Square/Elevation/Thickness/Width of line/Area/Dimensions]:
Specify the opposite corner of the rectangle.
Specify the rotation angle of the rectangle.
Begin creating a rectangle by specifying a corner of a square then:
Additional options [Chamfer/Fillet/Rotated/Elevation/Thickness/Width of line/Area/Dimensions]
Specify a corner along the same side of the square to define its length and angle.
Begin creating a rectangle by specifying its area then:

Choose whether to use the length or width to calculate the dimensions for the rectangle.
Length: Enter rectangle length
Width: Enter rectangle width

dd.p: Begin creating a rectangle by specifying its length then:

dlentry.dd: Specify the width of the rectangle.
Specify the first corner of the rectangle.
Additional options: [Chamfer/Fillet/Rotated/Square/Elevation/Thickness/Width of line/Area/Dimensions]:

section.title: Options within the RECTANG command
section.p: After you begin creating a rectangle, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the first chamfer distance to use for all rectangles then:
Additional options [turn chamfer Off, use Default setting]

dlentry.dt: Second chamfer distance to use for all rectangles
dlentry.dd: Specify the second chamfer distance to use for all rectangles
Specify the fillet distance to use for all rectangles.
Additional options [turn fillet Off, use Default setting]
Specify the height above the xy-plane to use for all rectangles.
Additional options: [use Default]:
Specify the width of the rectangle line segments. All segments have the same width.
Specify the thickness of the rectangle line segments. All segments have the same thickness.
Turn off chamfer.
Turn off fillet.
Reset the default value.
